analysis:
- some lines underscored in brown with crayon (rarely with pencil), or marked with "NB", or with the asterisk on margins;
- scarce annotations on margins, with 17th cent. hand, but most frequently just highlighting the underscored text or repeating its content;
- sometimes astonished reader comments with short words: writing "Mirum", or "Ubi hoc?" or "causa dubia".
The difficulty is that the annotations are written down with a brownish crayon which with the time has become fuzzy and hardly legible. Probably we will scan and publish online this copy as well, to preserve the reader-added content.
